                <ul class="nav nav-tabs" role="tablist">
                    <li class="active"><a data-toggle="tab" href="behat-loves-mink#tab-script">Script</a></li>
                    <li><a data-toggle="tab" href="behat-loves-mink#tab-comment">
                        <i class="fa fa-comment-o"></i>
                                                    
                                                                                                (6)
                                                                                        Conversation
                                            </a></li>
                </ul>

                <div class="tab-content">
                    <div class="tab-pane active" id="tab-script">
                        <div class="js-script-content-wrapper top-margin-script markdown-content">
                                                                                        <a href="https://github.com/knpuniversity/behat/edit/behat3/knpu/behat-loves-mink.md" target="_blank" class="btn btn-default btn-circle pull-right js-tooltip" title="Edit on GitHub"><span class="fa fa-pencil"></span></a>
                                                                    <p>Behat parses scenarios and Mink is really good at browsing the web.
If we combine their powers, we could start having steps that look
a lot like what we have in <code>search.feature</code>. </p>
