<p>This library ties Behat and Mink together and gives us two cool things. First, it
lets us access the Mink Session object inside of <code>FeatureContext</code>. We'll see that
soon.</p>
<p>For the second thing, add a new config called <code>suites:</code> and a key under that
called <code>default:</code> with a <code>contexts:</code> key. We'll talk about <code>suites</code> later. Under
<code>contexts</code>, pass <code>FeatureContext</code> <em>and</em>  <code>Behat\MinkExtension\Context\MinkContext</code>:</p>
