<p>Let's see what that gives us: run behat with the <code>-dl</code> option again:</p>
<pre><code class="language-bash"><div class="line">php vendor/bin/behat -dl</div></code></pre>
<p>Boom! Now we see a <em>huge</em> list! These include definitions for all common web actions, like
<code>When I go to</code> or <code>When I fill in "field" with "value"</code>. This includes the stuff we're
using inside of <code>search.feature</code>:</p>
